 Job Title:  Scientist, Systems Engineer (Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning (AI/ML)) 
Job Code: SAS20210305-60630 
Job Location: Palm Bay, FL 
Job Description:  AI/ML Systems Engineer experienced in architecting, implementing, testing, and troubleshooting hardware and software for various applications. The AI/ML Systems Engineer will assist with design and implementation of architectures for proposals and/or projects to build or enhance technical capabilities. This position assists in resolving complex system problems and interacts with program engineering, management, and customers. The position also requires the ability to lead and mentor team members in the lifecycle support of the artificial intelligence and machine learning systems and associated gear. 
Essential Functions:
 The candidate should be able to perform the following tasks with minimal oversight: 
Create system-level solutions for data fusion and optimization through conception and application of machine learning or machine intelligence 
Develop technology development roadmaps and investment strategies for near-term and long-term business growth 
Lead independent research and development projects and collaborate with multi-domain data scientists to develop novel techniques and capture intellectual property 
Create, write and review business proposals in relevant technology areas 
Develop and present architectures and concepts to internal and external customers 
Qualifications:
 PhD with 5 years of experience or Masters degree with 10 years of experience in a relevant field (computer science/engineering, optimization, machine learning) 
Experience in two or more of the following areas: machine learning, data mining, statistical modeling, optimization, algorithms, big-data, game theory, machine vision 
Strong communication skills with the ability to formally document, present and communicate complex ideas to audiences with diverse backgrounds 
Experience applying statistical or analytical methods to complex problems to develop production-ready solutions 
Published work in relevant technology areas 
Active TS/SCI or TS/SSBI security clearance required. 
Preferred Additional Skills: 
Experience improving features of, productizing and validating or creating trust in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning algorithms for use in real-world environments 
Expertise with one or more programming languages for the purposes of algorithm development: Matlab, C/C++, Python 
Experience optimizing for, and migrating learning models to field devices (edge processing) 
Experience directly interacting with customers to develop their technology roadmaps, identify opportunities for AI/ML technology insertion and/or create new business opportunities L3Harris 3 days ago original job Report job Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Scientist jobs in Palm Bay, FL Jobs at Technologies in Palm Bay, FL Scientist salaries in Palm Bay, FL Company Info Follow Get job updates from L3Harris Technologies L3Harris Technologies 4,571 reviews At L3Harris, we inspire excellence. Across air, land, sea, space and cyber domains, our customers perform on the worldâ€™s most challenging... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume Hiring Lab Career Advice Browse Jobs Browse Companies Salaries Find Certifications Indeed Events Work at Indeed Countries About Help Center Â© 2021 Indeed Do Not Sell My Personal Information Accessibility at Indeed Privacy Center Cookies Privacy Terms Let Employers Find You Upload Your Resume 
 
 
 
 
 
